  <brief_title>Identifying Methylation Biomarkers for Monitoring Bladder Tumors</brief_title>
  <official_title>Using PCR Technology (Polymerase Chain Reaction Technology) for Monitoring Patients With Bladder Tumors - Optimizing Genanalyses for Clinical Use.</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Copenhagen University Hospital at Herlev</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Copenhagen University Hospital at Herlev</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To investigate the methylation status of 4-6 genes in Urine and matching bladder tissue
      biopsies, in order to find methylation markers for use in a noninvasive test in monitoring
      patients with bladder tumors.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
